[[File:The cast and crew of 'Orange is the New Black' 2014.jpg|280px|left|thumb|Members of the cast and crew with their [[Peabody Award]], May 2014]]
''Orange Is the New Black'' has received critical acclaim. It has been particularly praised for humanizing prisoners<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/how-orange-is-the-new-black-humanizes-inmates/2013/07/26/d1559bac-f3e5-11e2-9434-60440856fadf_story.html |title=How 'Orange Is the New Black' humanizes inmates |website=[[The Washington Post]] |first=Seth |last=Abramson |date=July 26, 2013 |accessdate=September 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bustle.com/articles/28263-has-orange-is-the-new-black-changed-the-way-we-think-of-prisoners-former-inmates-say |title=Has 'Orange is the New Black' Changed the Way We Think of Prisoners? Former Inmates Say No, But There's Progress Ahead |website=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]] |first=Rachel |last=Simon |date=June 17, 2014 |accessdate=September 2, 2015}}</ref> and for its depiction of race, sexuality, gender and body types.<ref name="Great Orange grantland">{{cite web |url=http://grantland.com/hollywood-prospectus/the-great-orange-is-the-new-black-is-suddenly-the-best-netflix-binge-watch-series-yet/ |title=The Great Orange Is the New Black Is Suddenly the Best Netflix Series Yet |website=[[Grantland]] |first=Andy |last=Greenwald |date=July 15, 2013 |accessdate=September 1, 2015}}</ref><ref name="NYPost ignites">{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2014/06/04/orange-is-the-new-black-ignites-a-tv-revolution-for-women/ |title='Orange Is the New Black' ignites a TV revolution for women |website=[[New York Post]] |first=Robert |last=Rorke |date=June 4, 2014 |accessdate=September 2, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Caged">{{cite news |first=Mac |last=McClelland |url=http://contentviewer.adobe.com/s/Rolling%20Stone%20Magazine/57ff9f4987144d9c87ed088b3f6faba5/RS1237/0350.R1237_FEA_Orange.html |title=Caged Heat |journal=[[Rolling Stone]] |issue=1237 |date=June 18, 2015 |accessdate=January 5, 2018}}</ref><ref name="What Red Did">{{cite web |url=http://www.thewrap.com/orange-new-black-prison-sex-women-paleyfest-netflix/ |title='Orange Is the New Black' Cast Dishes on Prison Sex, Women Calling the Shots, and What Red Did |website=[[TheWrap]] |first=L.A. |last=Ross |date=March 15, 2014 |accessdate=September 2, 2015}}</ref><ref name="TVG Cox Breaks">{{cite web |url=http://www.tvguide.com/news/orange-new-black-laverne-cox-1068255/ |title=Trans Actress Laverne Cox Breaks New Ground with Orange Is the New Black |first=Sadie |last=Gennis |website=[[TV Guide]] |date=July 24, 2013 |accessdate=September 2, 2015}}</ref><ref name="DDot changed">{{cite web |url=http://www.dailydot.com/fandom/orange-new-black-fandom-feminism/ |title=How "Orange Is the New Black" changed the way we talk about TV |website=[[The Daily Dot]] |first=Audra |last=Schroeder |date=August 5, 2013 |accessdate=September 2, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Time New Way">{{cite web |url=http://entertainment.time.com/2013/07/25/dead-tree-alert-orange-is-the-new-black-is-the-new-way-of-talking-about-tv/ |title=Dead Tree Alert: Orange Is the New Black Is the New Way of Talking About TV |website=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |first=James |last=Poniewozik |date=July 25, 2013 |accessdate=September 2, 2015}}</ref>

The first season received positive reviews from critics. Review aggregator [[Metacritic]] gave it a [[Weighted arithmetic mean|weighted average]] score of 79 out of 100 based on reviews from 32 critics, indicating favorable reviews.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/critic-reviews |title=Critic Reviews for Orange Is the New Black Season 1 |publisher=Metacritic |year=2013 |accessdate=July 18, 2013}}</ref> On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], season one has a 94% approval rating based on 47 reviews, with an average rating of 8.24 out of 10 . The site's critical consensus is "''Orange Is the New Black'' is a sharp mix of [[black humor]] and dramatic heft, with interesting characters and an intriguing flashback structure."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/s01/ |title=Orange Is the New Black: Season 1 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |year=2013 |accessdate=August 16, 2014}}</ref>

Hank Stuever, television critic for ''[[The Washington Post]]'', gave ''Orange Is the New Black'' a perfect score. In his review of the series, he stated: "In Jenji Kohan's magnificent and thoroughly engrossing new series, ''Orange Is the New Black'', prison is still the pits. But it is also filled with the entire range of human emotion and stories, all of which are brought vividly to life in a world where a stick of gum could ignite either a romance or a death threat."<ref name="Hank">{{cite web |last=Steuver |first=Hank |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/tv/netflixs-orange-is-the-new-black-brilliance-behind-bars/2013/07/11/d52f911e-e9aa-11e2-8f22-de4bd2a2bd39_story.html |title=Netflix's ''Orange Is the New Black'': Brilliance behind bars |website=The Washington Post |date=July 11, 2013 |accessdate=August 8, 2013}}</ref> Maureen Ryan, of ''[[The Huffington Post]]'', wrote: "''Orange'' is one of the best new programs of the year, and the six episodes I've seen have left me hungry to see more."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/maureen-ryan/orange-is-the-new-black_b_3574249.html |title='Orange Is The New Black' Review: Subversive Netflix Prison Drama Proves Addictive |website=The Huffington Post |date=July 10, 2013 |accessdate=August 8, 2013 |last=Ryan |first=Maureen}}</ref>

The second season also received critical acclaim. Rotten Tomatoes gave a rating of 98%, with an average rating of 9.17 out of 10 based on 45 reviews. The site's critical consensus reads: "With a talented ensemble cast bringing life to a fresh round of serial drama, ''Orange Is the New Black's'' sophomore season lives up to its predecessor's standard for female-led television excellence."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/s02/ |title=Orange Is the New Black: Season 2 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |year=2014 |accessdate=August 16, 2014}}</ref> Metacritic gave the second season a score of 89 out of 100 based on 31 critics, indicating "universal acclaim."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/season-2/critic-reviews |title=Critic Reviews for Orange Is the New Black Season 2 |publisher=Metacritic |year=2014 |accessdate=August 16, 2014}}</ref> David Wiegland of the ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' gave the season a positive review, calling the first six episodes "not only as great as the first season, but arguably better."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sfgate.com/tv/article/Orange-Is-the-New-Black-review-Me-vs-we-5526099.php |title='Orange Is the New Black' review: Me vs. we |website=San Francisco Chronicle |first=David |last=Wiegland |date=June 3, 2014 |accessdate=June 11, 2015}}</ref>

The third season received critical acclaim. On Metacritic, it has a score of 83 out of 100 based on 24 reviews.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/season-3 |title=Orange Is the New Black: Season 3 |publisher=Metacritic |year=2015 |accessdate=June 16, 2015}}</ref> On Rotten Tomatoes, it has a 95% rating with an average score of 8.15 out of 10 based on 58 reviews. The site's critical consensus reads: "Thanks to its blend of potent comedy and rich character work, ''Orange is the New Black'' remains a bittersweet pleasure in its third season."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/s03/ |title=Orange Is the New Black: Season 3 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |year=2015 |accessdate=June 16, 2015}}</ref>

The fourth season received critical acclaim. On Metacritic, it has a score of 86 out of 100 based on 19 reviews.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/season-4 |title=Orange Is the New Black: Season 4 |publisher=Metacritic |year=2016 |accessdate=July 4, 2016}}</ref> On Rotten Tomatoes, it has a 96% rating with an average score of 8.46 out of 10 based on 47 reviews. The site's critical consensus reads: "''Orange is the New Black'' is back and better than ever, with a powerful fourth season full of compelling performances by the ensemble cast."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/s04/ |title=Orange Is the New Black: Season 4 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |year=2016 |accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref> James Poniewozik of ''The New York Times'' reviewed the fourth season as "Do you measure the quality of a TV season as a beginning-to-end average or by how well it ends? By the first yardstick, Season 4 is ambitious but uneven; by the latter, it's the series' best."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/24/arts/television/season-4-of-orange-is-the-new-black-its-about-time.html |title=Orange Is The New Black: It's About Time |website=The New York Times |first=James |last=Poniewozik |date=June 22, 2016 |accessdate=September 7, 2016}}</ref>

The fifth season received "generally favorable reviews".<ref name=MC>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/season-5 |title=Orange Is the New Black: Season 5 |publisher=Metacritic |year=2017 |accessdate=June 10, 2017}}</ref> On Metacritic, it has a score of 67 out of 100 based on 20 reviews.<ref name=MC /> On Rotten Tomatoes, it has a 73% rating with an average score of 7.19 out of 10 based on 41 reviews. The site's critical consensus reads: "''Orange Is the New Black''{{'}}s fifth season offers up more of the sharp writing and dizzying tonal juggling acts that fans expect – albeit somewhat less successfully."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/s05/ |title=Orange Is the New Black: Season 5 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |year=2017 |accessdate=June 10, 2017}}</ref>

The sixth season received positive reviews from critics, with many critics noting its improvement over the previous season. On Metacritic, it has a score of 69 out of 100 based on 14 reviews.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/season-6|title=Orange Is the New Black: Season 6 |publisher=Metacritic |year=2018 |accessdate=August 1, 2018}}</ref> On Rotten Tomatoes, it has an 84% rating with an average score of 7.3 out of 10 based on 32 reviews. The site's critical consensus reads: "Brutality and humor continue to mesh effectively in a season of ''Orange Is the New Black'' that stands as a marked improvement from its predecessor, even if some arcs are more inspired than others."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/orange-is-the-new-black/s06/ |title=Orange Is the New Black: Season 6 |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |year=2018 |accessdate=August 1, 2018}}</ref>

===Accolades===
{{Main|List of accolades received by Orange Is the New Black}}

''Orange Is the New Black'' has received many accolades since its debut. The series has garnered 16 [[Primetime Emmy Award|Emmy Award]] nominations and four wins. For its first season, it received 12 Emmy Award nominations, including [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Comedy Series|Outstanding Comedy Series]], [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Comedy Series|Outstanding Writing for a Comedy Series]], and [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Comedy Series|Outstanding Directing for a Comedy Series]], winning three.<ref name="Emmy">{{cite web |url=http://www.emmys.com/shows/orange-new-black |title=Orange Is The New Black |publisher=Television Academy |accessdate=April 14, 2016}}</ref> [[Taylor Schilling]] received a [[Golden Globe Award]] nomination for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress – Television Series Drama|Best Actress in a Television Series – Drama]].<ref name="GG">{{cite web |url=http://www.hfpa.org/browse/?param=/film/26477 |title=Orange is the New Black |publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]] |accessdate=June 11, 2015}}</ref> In 2013, the [[American Film Institute]] selected the series as one of the Top 10 Television Programs of the Year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.afi.com/afiawards/AFIAwards13.aspx |title=AFI Awards 2013 |publisher=American Film Institute |accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref>

A new Emmy rule in 2015, classifying half-hour shows as comedies and hour-long shows as dramas, forced the series to change categories from comedy to drama for its second season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vox.com/2015/7/16/8976181/emmys-nominations-comedy-drama |title=7 Emmys Rules and Quirks that Explain the 2015 Nominations |first=Todd |last=VanDerWerff |website=[[Vox (website)|Vox]] |date=July 16, 2015 |accessdate=September 1, 2015}}</ref> That year, the series received four Emmy nominations, including [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Drama Series|Outstanding Drama Series]], and Aduba won her second Emmy Award, for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series|Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series]].<ref name="Emmy" /> ''Orange Is the New Black'' became the first series to receive Emmy nominations in both comedy and drama categories.<ref name="Birnbaum" /> For its second season, the series also received three Golden Globe Award nominations: [[Golden Globe Award for Best Television Series – Musical or Comedy|Best Television Series – Musical or Comedy]], [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress – Television Series Musical or Comedy|Best Actress – Television Series Musical or Comedy]] for Schilling, and [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actress – Series, Miniseries or Television Film|Best Supporting Actress – Series, Miniseries or Television Film]] for Aduba. At the [[21st Screen Actors Guild Awards]], the series won [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Comedy Series]] and Aduba won [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Comedy Series]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/sag-award-winners-2015-screen-actors-guild-awards-winner-list-1201414657/ |title=SAG Award Winners 2015: Full List |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=January 25, 2015 |accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref>

For its third season, ''Orange Is the New Black'' won Screen Actors Guild Awards for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Comedy Series and Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Comedy Series (Aduba).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2016-sag-winners-complete-list-856945/item/outstanding-performance-by-a-female-846040 |title=SAG Awards: The Complete Winners List |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=January 30, 2016 |accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref> It received a Golden Globe Award nomination for Best Television Series – Musical or Comedy.<ref name="GG" /> The series has also received, among other accolades, six [[Writers Guild of America Award]] nominations,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://awards.wga.org/wga-awards/previous-nominees-winners |title=Previous Nominees & Winners |publisher=[[Writers Guild of America]] |accessdate=April 14, 2016}}</ref> five [[Satellite Awards]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pressacademy.com/award_cat/2013/ |title=2013 Satellite Awards |publisher=[[International Press Academy]] |accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pressacademy.com/award_cat/2015/ |title=2015 Satellite Awards |publisher=[[International Press Academy]] |accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref> four [[Critics' Choice Television Award]]s,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/critics-choice-television-awards-2014-712986 |title=Critics' Choice Television Awards 2014: Complete Winners List |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=June 19, 2014 |accessdate=April 15, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/critics-choice-television-awards-winners-2015-full-list-1201509015/ |title=Critics' Choice Awards Winners: Full List |website=Variety |date=May 31, 2015 |accessdate=April 15, 2016}}</ref> a [[GLAAD Media Award]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.glaad.org/blog/george-takei-orange-new-black-concussion-among-glaadawards-recipients-new-york-city |title=George Takei, "Orange is the New Black," "Concussion" among #GLAADAwards recipients in New York City |publisher=[[GLAAD]] |date=May 3, 2014 |accessdate=April 15, 2016}}</ref> an [[American Cinema Editors Awards 2016|American Cinema Editors Award]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/behind-screen/2016-ace-eddie-award-nominations-851748 |title='Star Wars' Among Nominees for ACE Eddie Awards for Film Editing |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=January 4, 2016 |accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref> a [[Producers Guild of America Award for Best Episodic Comedy|Producers Guild of America Award]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/pga-awards-orange-is-new-766654 |title=PGA Awards: 'Orange Is the New Black' Wins Outstanding Producer of Episodic Television, Comedy |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=January 24, 2015 |accessdate=April 14, 2016}}</ref> and a [[Peabody Award]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.peabodyawards.com/award-profile/orange-is-the-new-black-netflix |title=Orange is the New Black (Netflix) |publisher=Peabody Awards |accessdate=April 17, 2016}}</ref>

==Broadcast==
{{Quote box|width=270px|align=left| quote=Netflix is famously tight-fisted when it comes to offering up viewership data about its original series. But execs with the streaming giant have repeatedly confirmed that ''OITNB'' is its most-watched original series. That has been backed up by the efforts of outside measurement companies to track viewing in the Netflix eco-system.|source=—''Variety''<ref name="rating" />}}

The series began airing on broadcast television in [[New Zealand]] on [[TVNZ 2|TV2]] on August 19, 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvnz.co.nz/orange-is-the-new-black/index-group-5523557 |title=Orange Is The New Black |publisher=TVNZ |accessdate=August 22, 2013}}</ref> It premiered in [[Australia]] on October 9, 2013, on [[Showcase (Australian TV channel)|Showcase]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2013/09/airdate-orange-is-the-new-black.html |title=Airdate: Orange is the New Black |publisher=TV Tonight |date=September 9, 2013 |first=David |last=Knox |accessdate=December 5, 2013}}</ref> The second season began on Showcase on July 16, 2014,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxtel.com.au/got/whats-on/foxtel-insider/foxtel/most-anticipated-returning-shows.html |title=Most anticipated returning shows in 2014 |publisher=Foxtel |date=January 14, 2014 |accessdate=July 26, 2014}}</ref> and the third season premiered on June 11, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxtel.com.au/got/whats-on/foxtel-insider/showcase/orange-is-the-new-black.html |title=Orange is the New Black S3: same time as the US |publisher=Foxtel |date=June 4, 2015 |accessdate=June 11, 2015}}</ref> The first season began airing on broadcast television in the [[United Kingdom|UK]] on [[Sony Channel (UK and Ireland)|Sony Channel]] from April 19, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/orange-is-new-black-uk-linear-rights-go-sony-channel-988468 |title=Sony Channel U.K. Takes 'Orange Is the New Black' |last=Szalai |first=Georg |date=March 24, 2017 |website=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=March 24, 2017}}</ref>

In April 2017, it was reported that a [[Cybercrime|cybercriminal]] had stolen the first ten episodes of the fifth season in a security breach of a post-production company. Netflix failed to respond to ransom demands, and the cybercriminal [[internet leak|leaked]] the episodes online. Netflix confirmed the security breach and an ongoing investigation by federal law enforcement.<ref name="S5 Leaked">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hacker-threatens-release-new-episodes-orange-is-new-black-998670 |title=Hacker Releases New Episodes of 'Orange Is the New Black |website=The Hollywood Reporter |agency=Associated Press |date=April 28, 2017 |accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/29/business/media/netflix-hack-orange-is-the-new-black.html |title=Hacker Leaks Episodes From Netflix Show and Threatens Other Networks |website=The New York Times |last1=Perlroth |first1=Nicole |last2=Haag |first2=Matthew |date=April 29, 2017 |accessdate=April 30, 2017}}</ref> ''[[Multichannel News]]'' reported that demand for the series significantly increased over the seven-day period following the leak of the episodes. It was also said that the leak would likely cause a decrease in demand for the fifth season when Netflix releases it in June.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.multichannel.com/blog/bauminator/demand-orange-new-black-spiked-following-hack/412744 |title=Demand for 'Orange Is the New Black' Spiked Following Hack |website=[[Multichannel News]] |date=May 10, 2017 |first=Jeff |last=Baumgartner |accessdate=May 11, 2017}}</ref>

===Ratings===
''Orange Is the New Black'' generated more viewers and hours viewed in its first week than the other top Netflix original series ''[[House of Cards (U.S. TV series)|House of Cards]]'' and ''[[Arrested Development (TV series)|Arrested Development]]''.<ref name="Grantland">{{cite web |url=http://grantland.com/features/orange-is-the-new-black-netflix-season-two/ |title=Brilliant 'Orange' |website=[[Grantland]] |first=Andy |last=Greenwald |date=June 4, 2014 |accessdate=September 1, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://allthingsd.com/20130723/netflixs-no-name-show-beating-house-of-cards-and-arrested-development/ |title=Netflix's No-Name Show Beating "House of Cards" and "Arrested Development" |website=[[All Things Digital]] |date=July 23, 2013 |accessdate=December 10, 2013 |last=Kafka |first=Peter}}</ref> In October 2013, Netflix stated that the show is a "tremendous success" for the streaming platform. "It will end the year as our most watched original series ever and, as with each of our other previously launched originals, enjoys an audience comparable with successful shows on cable and broadcast TV."<ref>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2013/10/21/netflix-orange-is-the-new-black-most-watched/ |title=Netflix: 'Orange Is The New Black' Is Our Most-Watched Original, But Our TV Exclusives Are Even Bigger |website=[[TechCrunch]] |first=Anthony |last=Ha |date=October 21, 2013 |accessdate=February 12, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://mashable.com/2013/10/21/orange-is-the-new-black-netflix-most-watched/#YHlOr3Wcb8qw |title='Orange Is the New Black' Is Netflix's Most-Watched Original Series |website=[[Mashable]] |first=Brian Anthony |last=Hernandez |date=October 21, 2013 |accessdate=April 19, 2016}}</ref> As reported in February 2016, ''Orange Is the New Black'' remains Netflix's most-watched original series.<ref name="rating" /><ref name="rating2">{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/netflix-renews-orange-is-the-new-black-for-three-more-series-a6855626.html |title=Netflix renews Orange is the New Black for three more series |website=[[The Independent]] |first=Jess |last=Denham |date=February 5, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2016/feb/05/orange-is-the-new-black-renewed-new-season-netflix |title=Orange is the New Black renewed for three additional seasons |website=[[The Guardian]] |first=Nigel M |last=Smith |date=February 5, 2016 |accessdate=April 19, 2016}}</ref> In 2016, a ''[[The New York Times|New York Times]]'' study of the 50 TV shows with the most [[List of Facebook features#Likes and Reactions|Facebook Likes]] found that ''Orange Is the New Black'' is one of the shows most watched in [[urban area]]s, and despite its "minority-rich ensemble cast," the series "appeals more to a white audience."<ref name="katz20161227">{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2016/12/26/upshot/duck-dynasty-vs-modern-family-television-maps.html |title='Duck Dynasty' vs. 'Modern Family': 50 Maps of the U.S. Cultural Divide |last=Katz |first=Josh |date=December 27, 2016 |accessdate=December 28, 2016 |website=The New York Times}}</ref>

